{ Is an inferior line leading to some Pirc/Benoni pawn structures that are good for White. Black's strategy is to create an unbalanced position and outplay White at some point. This is usually played by stronger players against lower rated oppositions, but it can appear anytime, so we need to know some key ideas. }
4. d4 { We are threatening to take on c5 and go for a better endgame. } 4...
cxd4
{ Allowing White to develop the Knight on c3, can only make things worse for Black. }
5. cxd4 Nf6 6. Nc3 g6
{ Black is developing the Bishop to g7, fighting for the d4 square so we need to play a little bit prophylactic: }
7. h3
{ Avoiding Bg4 that would trade White's Knight which is an important defender of the d4 square! }
7... Bg7 8. Bd3 O-O 9. O-O b5 10. e5
{ Black is one tempo short with the Queen-side play. } 10... Nfd7 11. Be4 Ra7
12. Bf4 { Black is struggling to finish his development. } *

