3... Qa5
{ Is a funny move that can take some club players by surprise, but in fact, developing the Queen this early is quite poor. }
4. Be2 d6 5. d4 { But we can go d4 anyway! } 5... cxd4 6. O-O
{ We are having a very good version of the Morra Gambit! } 6... dxc3 7. Nxc3
Nf6 8. Nd5 { Forcing Black more or less to take it. } 8... Nxd5 9. exd5 Nd7 10.
Re1 Nf6 11. Bc4 { Defending the pawn. } 11... Bg4 12. Bf4 Rc8 13. Bb3 Bxf3 14.
Qxf3
{ White has the Bishop pair, and Black has a really tough task to develop the rest of his King-side. }
*

