{ I think this is one of the riskiest lines that Black can go for. He is transposing to some very sharp lines of the Alapin with a6 played which is not useful at all here! }
4. e5 Nd5 5. d4 cxd4 6. Bc4
{ Going for the sharpest line possible because a6 is useless! } 6... Nb6 7. Bb3
d5 8. exd6 { Opening it up. } 8... Qxd6 9. O-O Nc6 10. cxd4 e6 11. Nc3 Be7 12.
Re1 O-O 13. a3 { A nice move, not allowing any Nb4 to d5. } 13... Nd5 14. Qd3
Bd7 15. Bc2 { Setting up the battery! } 15... g6 16. Bh6 Rfd8 17. Bb3
{ Now that g6 was played the Bishop was pointless on that diagonal, so we go back to b3! }
17... Rac8 18. Ne4 Qb8 19. Ba2 Be8 20. Rad1 b5 21. h4
{ White is having the initiative on the King-side. } *

