{ Has been played by Artemiev a few times with good results, although I think that White is able to get a pleasant position. }
6. Be2
{ Developing the Bishop, defending the Knight, and preparing to question the g4 Bishop with h3. }
6... Nf6 7. h3 Bh5 8. c4
{ Expanding in the center with c4-d5 is a good idea if Black allows it by not going cxd4! }
8... Qd6 9. d5
{ This pawn is very annoying on d5 because is stopping Black from developing his Knight to the most natural square c6. }
9... e6 10. Nc3 exd5 11. cxd5 Nbd7 12. O-O Be7 13. Nd2
{ A strong maneuver for the Knight, threatening to jump either on c4 or e4 to attack the enemy Queen. }
13... Bxe2 14. Qxe2 Nb6 15. Nde4 Nxe4 16. Qxe4
{ White is going to finish his development by playing Bf4, with a better position. }
*

