{ The main move, going for a traditional Alapin where the a6 move is pretty useful compared to what we have seen so far. }
5. d4 Nc6 6. dxc5
{ It works very well here because the Queen is unable to return to c7 because the Knight on c6 is blocking it! }
6... Qxc5 7. Be3
{ Notice how Black would love to play Qc7 here, but the Knight on c6 is not allowing it, so Black has to lose a couple of extra tempi. }
7... Qa5 8. Nbd2 Bf5 9. Nc4 Qc7 10. Bb6 { Attacking the Queen. } 10... Qd7 11.
Qxd7+ Bxd7 12. Bc7
{ White has a big lead in development and is threatening to play   12...--  13.Nb6  next. }
