6... Qxd1+
{ Going for the endgame might be Black's best chance, but being a pawn down is not ideal. }
7. Kxd1 Bg4
{ Has been the most played move in this position but White can keep the c5 pawn alive: }
8. Be3 Bxf3+ 9. gxf3 O-O-O+ 10. Kc2
{ A very safe square for the King now that there is no Bishop that can come to f5. }
10... Nf6 11. Nd2 Nd5 12. Nc4
{ The Knight is very strong on c4 hinting to the weak b6 square. } 12... Kc7
13. b4 { White is up a pawn. } *

