f3 { A solid move, defending the e4 pawn and limiting the b7 Bishop! } 15... b4
16. Nb1 { We don't mind the c2 pawn, the Knight is heading to c4! } 16... Qxc2
17. Nd2 Qxb2 18. Bf1
{ Black is risking his Queen for two pawns! We are threatening to play Rdc1 and Nc4. }
