15... Bxb2 16. Rxb2 e6 17. Nb4 { Inviting Black to take it! } 17... Qc7 18.
Nxc6 Bxc6 { Not defending a6, but has a tactical point: } 19. c4 bxc4 20. Bxc4
Bxe4 { Was Black's idea. } 21. Qxe4 d5 22. Qe3
{ Getting ready to hunt the Black King. } 22... dxc4 23. bxc4 Nc5 24. Rbd2
{ White is better because the d-file belongs to him, and Black's King is potentially vulnerable due to the lack of a Fianchetto Bishop. }
