11... dxe5 12. Nxe5 { Recapturing the pawn, and preparing Qf3. } 12... O-O 13.
Qf3 { Going for the Achilles' heel! The pawn on c6 is weak. } 13... Bb7 14. Qe3
{ Trying to stop Black from pushing c5, and open up the b7 Bishop. } 14... Rfd8
{ Black is placing the Rook on the open file. } 15. Nc4
{ Forcing Black to go for a worse endgame. } 15... Qxe3 16. Bxe3
{ Developing the Bishop and connecting the Rooks. } 16... Ng4 17. Bc1
{ We have to be careful with the b2 pawn because Black had some Ba6 ideas. }
17... Ba6 18. Nca5 { Attacking the c6 pawn. } 18... Rac8 19. h3
{ Making a luft, and attacking the Knight. } 19... Ne5 20. Bg5
{ Developing the last piece, and attacking the e7 pawn. } 20... f6
{ Black had to close his own Bishop. } 21. Be3
{ White's Knights are more active than Black's Bishops. White is better because Black's Queen-side is weak. }
