8. Be3 { Developing the Bishop, attacking the c5 pawn. } 8... b6 9. a4
{ Threatening to play a5 to undermine the c5 pawn, and activate our Rook. }
9... e5 { Is ignoring White's idea. } 10. a5 { Threatening to take on b6. }
10... Ba6 { Was played in a few correspondence games. } 11. Qd2
{ Developing the Queen, keeping Bh6 ideas. } 11... Qe7 12. axb6
{ Opening the a file. } 12... axb6 13. O-O { Getting our King to safety. }
13... Bb7 14. Bh6
{ We are going to trade the Bishops, and follow up with Ne2, Nh2 and push f4. }
