5. d3 Bg7 6. h3 Nf6 7. Nc3 Nd7 8. Be3 e5 9. Qd2 { Threatening to play Bh6. }
9... h6 { Stopping White from playing Bh6. } 10. O-O Qe7
{ Used to be the Main-Move for a while, but White gets easy play. } 11. Nh2
{ Preparing to push f4. } 11... Nf8 12. f4 { The point of going Nh2! } 12...
exf4 13. Bxf4 { In my repertoire we always take on f4 with the Bishop! } 13...
