15. Qe1 { Avoiding the Queen trade, and defending the Bishop. } 15... Nd4 16.
Qf2 { Defending c2, and attacking f7 in the same time. } 16... O-O 17. Bd6
{ Forcing Black to make a drastic decision! } 17... Bxh3
{ Forced, otherwise White wins the exchange for free. } 18. Bf4
{ Forcing Black to go for the piece down endgame. } 18... Qxg2+ 19. Qxg2
{ Taking the Queen. } 19... Bxg2 20. Kxg2 { Recapturing the Bishop. } 20... g5
{ Was the point in the 10...b6 line, the idea was to get rid of the Bishop and take on c2 attacking the a1 Rook, and threatening to fork on e3! }
21. Bd6
{ But here we can just go for the pawn since there is no b6 on the board! }
21... Nxc2 22. Bxc5
{ A strong intermezzo! Threatening to play Rac1 next, and also not allowing Black any Ne3 jumps! }
22... Nxa1 23. Bxf8 { Taking the Rook. } 23... Rxf8 24. Rxa1
{ White should be technically winning i think with a Knight for two pawns. } *

