5. d3 Qc7
{ An interesting sideline, Black wants to play similar to the English Opening: e5-f6 and then Nh6-Nf7 is a common idea. }
6. O-O { We are not afraid of Bg4. } 6... e5 7. a4
{ Grabbing space on the Queen-side. } 7... Nf6
{ Doesn't really fit that well with Qc7 but i found a nice maneuver for White. }
8. Qd2 { Preparing either Qc3 or Qg5. } 8... a5
{ Tries to stop White from gaining aditional space on the Queen-side. } 9. Qg5
{ Attacking the e5 pawn. } 9... Nd7 10. Qg3 { Keeping an eye on the e5 pawn. }
10... Bg7 11. h4 { Typical idea for Lc0, always throwing in the h pawn! } 11...
O-O 12. h5
{ White gets ready to open up the h file, that can later be used to attack the enemy King. }
12... Re8 13. hxg6 { Opening up the h file. } 13... hxg6 14. Be3
{ Developing the Bishop, keeping an eye on the c5 pawn. } 14... b6 15. Nbd2
{ White has annoying pressure on the King-side based on the Qh4-Ng5 combo. } *

