b6 11. Nc4 { Attacking b6 and preparing Qd2, questioning the h6 Knight. } 11...
Ra6 12. Qd2 { Forcing Black to make a shameful retreat. } 12... Ng8 13. e5
{ Stopping Black from developing the Knight. } 13... Be6 14. Rb3
{ Preparing to double the Rooks on the b file. } 14... Bxc4 15. dxc4
{ Recapturing the Bishop. } 15... Qxd2+ 16. Kxd2
{ White will play Rfb1 and collect the Queen-side. } *

