5. d3 Bg7 6. h3 Qc7
{ This line is recommended by Christof Sielecki in his Sveshnikov Course.It is similar with the 5...Qc7 but a little bit worse since Black lost flexibility with the dark squared Bishop. }
7. O-O e5 8. a3 { Works well here because Black is behind in development! }
8... a5
{ Is a common reaction when White goes a3.The point is to slow down White's Queen-Side play. }
9. Be3 b6 10. Nbd2 Ne7 11. Nc4 a4 12. b4 { Continuing the initiative! } 12...
b5 13. Na5
{ The Knight is very strong on the edge here because it's putting a lot of pressure on Black's Queen-Side! }
13... cxb4 14. axb4 O-O 15. c4 { Putting pressure on the Queen-Side. } 15...
Rd8 16. Qc1 { Threatening to take on b5. } 16... Ba6 17. Ra3
{ White has the initiative on the Queen-Side. } *

