6. O-O { Avoiding the trap for now. } 6... d6
{ The plan of going d6-e5 is inferior here, because White has the simple and effective plan of going c3-d4. }
7. c3 Nf6 8. Re1 e5 9. d4 cxd4 10. cxd4 Bg4 11. Nbd2
{ Keeping a nice coordination, threatening to recapture on f3 with the Knight and having good control in the center. }
11... Be7 12. h3 Bh5 13. Qc2 O-O 14. b3
{ We prepare to bring our Bishop to another diagonal and connect the Rooks. }
14... Rac8 15. Bb2 Nd7 16. Rac1
{ White has a strong center and pressure on the c6 pawn. White went on to win in the game: 1-0 @@StartBracket@@43@@EndBracket@@ Grischuk,A @@StartBracket@@2720@@EndBracket@@-Zhang,P @@StartBracket@@2613@@EndBracket@@ Beersheba 2005 }
