O-O 14. h4
{ White is hunting the g6 Knight with h5 next, and also the d6 pawn is vulnerable. White has a safe game here with no weaknesses. Black managed to hold in a correspondence game, but I think it would be way trickier for a human to defend here.  Beveridge, C. @@StartBracket@@2153@@EndBracket@@ - Fremmegaard, J. @@StartBracket@@2225@@EndBracket@@ ICCF email, 2018. 33 moves, @@StartBracket@@½-½@@EndBracket@@. }
