1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5
{ Going for the Rossolimo! I've decided to pick this opening because it's giving us the following advantages:    • We are avoiding a lot of complex theory  • We are going to have a strategical battle @@StartBracket@@most Sicilian players are very gifted tactical players@@EndBracket@@    • We are going to be better prepared than our opponent @@StartBracket@@most of the players are focusing on Open Sicilians, not on Anti-Sicilians@@EndBracket@@    • We are still playing for an opening advantage, the Rossolimo is the main weapon of top players such as Fabiano Caruana, Magnus Carlsen, Levon Aronian, Anand Viswanathan, Michael Adams, and so on. }
3... e6
{ A very dynamical line! We can draw this conclusion by looking at the main ambassadors of this line: the Magician from Riga Alexei Shirov, and El Niño from Baku Teimour Radjabov, both known for their hyper-aggressive playing style. I think this line reached its peak in 2012 when Boris Gelfand used it 3 times in his World Championship match against Vishy Anand. From that point on the line has not been repeated in a World Championship Match, but it's still played quite often at all levels.   Black prepares to bring his King's Knight to e7 and then to put the question to White's Bishop, with the move ...a7-a6. In this case, the exchange on c6 will be favourable for Black, because he will recapture with the Knight and keep a healthy pawn structure. }
4. Bxc6
{ This is the move which Viacheslav Andreevich Chebanenko used to recommend to his pupils. Nothing is attacking the Bishop on b5, but nevertheless, White voluntarily exchanges it for the Knight. Now a very interesting position arises, with Black having doubled pawns. In addition, in this structure, he will not find it easy to activate his Bishop on c8. }
4... bxc6 5. d3
{ I decided to pick this line over  5.b3  that was played in the match for the World Crown in 2012 between Anand and Gelfand. The point of  5.d3  is that we are solidifying the e4 pawn, and we are staying flexible with the Bishop. You will see that in some positions it makes sense to go for b3-Bb2. }
5... Ne7 { The old main line. } 6. Qe2
