{ Recapturing the pawn, and protecting e4. } 11... Nd7 12. Nc3
{ Developing the Knight. } 12... e6 13. Qg3
{ Preparing Bf4 to attack the d6 pawn. } 13... Qe7 14. Nd5
{ White had the initiative in the game. Caruana probably missed that   14...exd5  is answered by the strong intermezzo  15.Bg5! }
*

