{ Taking the pawn. } 9... Rg8 10. d4 { Defending the Knight. } 10... h6 11. Nf3
{ Retreating the Knight. } 11... Bxh3 12. dxe5 { Going for a better endgame. }
12... dxe5 13. Qxd8+ { Trading the Queens for a better endgame. } 13... Rxd8
14. Nbd2 { Preparing Nc4. } 14... Be6 15. Nc4 { Attacking e5. } 15... Ng4 16.
Nb6 { Preparing Nd5. } 16... Na5 17. Nd5
{ White has a dominant Knight in the center of the board and a clear advantage even though this game eventually ended in a draw. }
*

