3... Qb6
{ Is pretty similar to 3...Qc7, but the difference is that this move is attacking the Bishop on b5. }
4. Nc3
{ Developing the Knight, defending the Bishop, and threating Nd5 sometimes. }
4... Nd4 5. Nxd4 { Creating doubled pawns for Black on the d file. } 5... cxd4
6. Nd5
{ Attacking the Queen, threatening to fork Black on c7 if he takes the Bishop. }
6... Qxb5 7. Nc7+ Kd8 8. Nxb5 { White is up a Queen. } *

