1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5
{ Going for the Rossolimo! I've decided to pick this opening because it's giving us the following advantages:    • We avoid a lot of complex theory    • We are going to have a strategical battle @@StartBracket@@most Sicilian players are very gifted tactical players!@@EndBracket@@    • We are going to be better prepared than our opponent @@StartBracket@@most of the players are focusing on the Open Sicilians, not on Anti-Sicilians.@@EndBracket@@    • We are still playing for an opening advantage, the Rossolimo is the main weapon of top players such as Fabiano Caruana, Magnus Carlsen, Levon Aronian, Anand Viswanathan, Michael Adams, and so on. }
3... e5
{ Is an interesting sideline, Black's point is to play Nge7 next, and follow up with the simple King-side Fianchetto. }
4. O-O Bd6 { Was recently tried by Magnus Carlsen a few times. } 5. c3 a6 6.
Ba4 b5 7. Bc2 Nge7 8. d3
{ I like the simple approach of Caruana. We are playing now a Ruy Lopez type of position with the misplaced Bishop on d6. }
8... O-O 9. Be3 Bb7 10. Nh4
{ A strong prophylactic move, keeping an eye on the f5 break. } 10... Re8 11.
Nd2 Ng6 12. Nf5 Bf8 13. Qg4 d6 14. h4
{ White has an improved version of the Ruy Lopez and went on to win in: 1-0 @@StartBracket@@57@@EndBracket@@ Caruana,F @@StartBracket@@2835@@EndBracket@@-Carlsen,M  @@StartBracket@@2863@@EndBracket@@ Lichess.org INT 2020 }
