3... Qc7
{ A normal move, the idea of which is to prevent the doubling of the pawns on c6. }
4. O-O { Getting our King to safety. } 4... Nf6 5. Re1 { Defending e4. } 5...
e6 6. e5 { Attacking the Knight. } 6... Nd5 7. c4
{ Attacking the Knight, preparing d3. } 7... Nb6 8. Bxc6
{ Trading the Bishop for the Knight because on b5, it was getting out of play. }
8... bxc6 9. d3 { Defending c4. } 9... d5 10. b3
