{ Sacrificing the Knight, preparing to take on g7 with the Bishop. } 7... fxe6
8. Bxg7 { Taking the pawn, and the Rook next. } 8... Qh4 9. Qf3
{ Defending f2, and preparing to collect the Rook next. You can analyze this further, but I think it's fair to stop and say that White will end up on top after the complications. It's important to remember the motif on 7.Nxe6 and you should be fine. }
