{ Developing the Bishop, defending the e4 pawn. } 7... Be7 8. Qe2
{ Developing the Queen. } 8... O-O 9. Bb2 Nc6 10. Nxc6 Bxc6 11. O-O
{ I personally like short castle, but you can go for 0-0-0 if you are feeling adventurous. }
11... Qc7 12. f4 { Grabbing space, preparing Rf3-Rh3. } 12... d5 13. e5
{ Entering into the French structure. } 13... Nd7 14. Rf3
{ White is threatening Bxh7 already, and has the initiative on the King-side. }
